<br>
     I, myself, have sat in PoT or PoK (and the other planes) trying to get groups. The only way I can seem to get a group is to start one, which gets really annoying after a while. What we Magicians need is a spell that makes us useful in groups. We don't need any raid enhancments, just some spell(s) that make us useful for simple little experience groups.<br>
<br>
     We all know that VI doesn't like soloing. PoP was designed so most classes wouldn't be able to solo. VI wants us to group. This is supposed to be a social game. All we can really do in groups is do damage, and that's pretty much everyone's job, isn't it?<br>
<br>
     I really wish that VI would give us a spell(s) to make us useful in groups. I've thought up some ideas. How about a 5 second casting time, 2 minute recast, 500 mana costing elemental that will rise, cast 3 or 4 &quot;Greater Healing&quot; spells on your target, then kill itself. Or, how about an elemental that will rise and cast mez on the targeted mob 5 times, each time after the first mez breaks, then kill itself. These are just some suggestions, but you see what I am getting at.<br>
<br>
     So, it's all up to you VI. Please post here with your comments. Whether you think something like this is a good idea, or a bad idea. Like I said before, I have been thinking about this for a long time, and would like to know what the mage community thinks of it.<br>
<br>
Sebor Robes<br>
