<br>
Our DPS is second only to Wizzies (yes, even higher than rogues and monks), and we still bring the extras to groups.<br>
<br>
If people aren't picking you up for groups, try and find out why.  If people say &quot;nah, we don't want a mage&quot; ask them why not?  Maybe they just don't realize how much damage you can do.  Sometimes it's levels.  if given the choice between a L65 mage and a L58 mage, who are both LFG, I'll pick the L65 mage every time - more damage, less resists, better spells (in general).  Depending on your level, try other zones - Seb, Velks, Maiden's, Umbral all seem to cater to the L62 and under crowd because the mobs are easier and give decent exp.  Do you get into OOC debates about how you can't get in a group, how no one wants you in a group, or anything?  If so, people remember &quot;we don't want the whiny kid&quot; type of thing.<br>
<br>
There could be all sorts of reasons - but usually, it's because people don't know.  When you tell them what you can do, hopefully they will wise up!<br>
